1.00	Adaios	Adaeus	Adaios, (lived ca. 450 BCE) also known as Adaeus, was a Macedonian poet of whomh little is known, save that he made two notable contributions to literature and history. When his good friend Euripides died in exile and was refused burial in his native Athens, Adaios composed the epitaph that graced the playwright's grave in Macedonia. Adaios' other noted achievement was his sage advice for those men who would know the pleasures of another male:	
